        <updateDate>2022-04-08T14:46:33Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Empower Parents to Protect Their Kids Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill prohibits an elementary or secondary school from receiving federal funds unless the school complies with specified requirements related to parental consent and student gender identity.</p> <p>Among other requirements, school employees may not withhold information from parents about a minor student's gender transition or gender identity. The Department of Justice or a parent or guardian may bring a civil action against a school for violations.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
